<p>
	Massage oils produce a beautiful mix of scents, sensations, emotions and feelings.</p>
<p>
	There are many pre-mixed massage oils on the market, making it easy to pick something up off the shelf to serve a particular purpose. It&#39;s much more satisfying though to create a unique and personal combination of oils to produce the exact mix for the desired results.</p>
<h3>
	How can I make my own massage oil?</h3>
<p>
	Making your own massage oil is the simple combination of a carrier oil and then adding essential oils.</p>
<p>
	<a href="http://www.avena.co.uk/search-results/?S=carrier%20oils">Carrier oils</a> are also known as base oils and dilute the added essential oils. They are available in a wide range of different viscosities depending on the requirements.</p>
<p>
	Depending on the skin type and sensitivity of the person being massaged, there are a range of carrier oils to choose from.</p>
<p>
	<a href="http://www.avena.co.uk/Apricot-Kernel-Oil-Prunus-Armeniaca/">Apricot Kernel</a> is a great choice and is popular for dehydrated or sensitive skin. <a href="http://www.avena.co.uk/Arnica-Oil-Arnica-Montana/">Arnica oil</a> has been used for centuries as an anti-inflammatory to relieve sprains, joint pain and tendon or ligament issues.</p>
<p>
	After a carrier oil has been selected, the <a href="http://www.avena.co.uk/essential-oils/">essential oil, or oils</a> are added. There is a huge range available and the choice depends on the desired sensation or outcome of the massage. <a href="http://www.avena.co.uk/Bergamot-Essential-Oil-Citrus-Bergamia/">Bergamot</a> is great for getting to sleep, <a href="http://www.avena.co.uk/Cardamom-Organic-Essential-Oil-Elettaria-cardamomum/">Cardamom</a> is good for helping with a cold, <a href="http://www.avena.co.uk/Lemongrass-Essential-Oil-Cymbopogon-citratus/">Lemongrass</a> relieves stress and <a href="http://www.avena.co.uk/Niaouli-Essential-Oil-Melaleuca-viridiflora/">Niaouli oil</a> is fantastic for skin conditions such as acne or for fighting infections.</p>
<p>
	It&#39;s important to know which oils can be used at any one time, particularly if the massage is to take place on someone who is pregnant or has a medical condition such as asthma. This is because some oils are not suitable or advised.</p>
<p>
	Making your own essential oils is a very personal and enriching experience. It&#39;s sure to produce fantastic results and is an excellent way to experiment with scents and sensations.&nbsp;</p>
